---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
const crates = [
  { name: "vihaco", blurb: "The framework: instructions, messages, effects, components, observers, composites, modules, syntax, runtime." },
  { name: "vihaco_cpu", blurb: "A ready-made CPU/host component and its instruction set." },
  { name: "vihaco_parser", blurb: "The #[derive(Parse)] proc-macro." },
  { name: "vihaco_parser_core", blurb: "The Parse trait and primitive parser impls." },
];
---
<Base title="API Reference" current="reference">
  <article class="shell narrow">
    <div class="titleblock">
      <p class="eyebrow">Reference</p>
      <h1>API Reference</h1>
      <p class="byline">
        This site is the guide-style documentation. The full Rust API
        reference is the generated rustdoc for the workspace crates.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="hosted"><span class="sec-num">§ 1</span>Hosted rustdoc</h2>
    <p>
      The generated rustdoc is published alongside this site under the
      <code>rust-api/</code> path. Entry points:
    </p>
    <dl class="crate-list">
      {crates.map((c) => (
        <>
          <dt><a href={`${base}/rust-api/${c.name}/index.html`}><code>{c.name.replace(/_/g, "-")}</code></a></dt>
          <dd>{c.blurb}</dd>
        </>
      ))}
    </dl>

    <h2 id="local"><span class="sec-num">§ 2</span>Build it locally</h2>
    <p>To generate the same API docs from a checkout:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">cargo doc --workspace --no-deps --open</code></pre>
    <p>Common entry points in the generated output:</p>
<pre><code>target/doc/vihaco/index.html
target/doc/vihaco_cpu/index.html
target/doc/vihaco_parser/index.html
target/doc/vihaco_parser_core/index.html</code></pre>

    <p>
      For a live local preview of <em>this</em> guide site instead, run
      <code>npm run dev</code> in <code>docs/</code>.
    </p>

    <h2 id="guides"><span class="sec-num">§ 3</span>Looking for the concepts?</h2>
    <p>
      The rustdoc documents every type and method. To learn how the pieces fit
      together — instruction encoding, the message/effect data flow, the parser
      pipeline, composing a machine — start with the
      <a href={`${base}/guide`}>Guides</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
